Package: HadesPrerequisites
Title: Check for system dependecies required by the OHDSI R
    packages
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Adam",
           family = "Black",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "adam.black@odysseusinc.com")
Description: HADES (formally known as the OHDSI Methods Library)
    is a set of open source R packages for large scale analytics,
    including population characterization, population-level causal effect
    estimation, and patient-level prediction.  HadesPrerequisites is a
    simple packages that checks system prerequisites needed to
    successfully install HADES.  If HadesPrerequisites installs
    successfully then the user should be confident that the rest of the
    OHDSI R packages will also install and load successfully.  Learn more
    at <https://ohdsi.github.io/Hades/>.
License: Apache License (>= 2.0)
URL: https://ohdsi.github.io/Hades
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.2)
